Thando Hopa attends the 2018 Pirelli Calendar Launch Gala at Manhattan Center on November 10, 2017 in New York City. JOHANNESBURG - The Miss South Africa 2019 judging has been announced ahead of the pageant on Friday. Model Thando Hopa, radio host Anele Mdoda, former Miss Universe Demi-Leigh Nel-Peters, reigning Miss Universe Catriona Gray, and actress Connie Ferguson will be choosing the new Miss SA 2019. WATCH: Miss SA CEO clarifies 'plus-size' model controversy The main event will be hosted by Bonang Matheba while Liesl Laurie and Zavion Kotze will be on the red carpet to unpack the outfits. Crowds will be entertained by several performers including Amanda Black and Sho Madjozi. The pageant, which is set to take place at Time Square in Pretoria, will be televised live and simulcast on M-Net and Mzansi Magic. Reigning Miss Universe @catriona_gray joins her predecessor @demileighnp , @thandohopa @zintathu and @connie_ferguson to choose Miss South Africa 2019. A post shared by  Miss South Africa (@official_misssa) on Aug 5, 2019 at 7:00am PDT OFFICIAL JUDGES! Reigning Miss Universe @catriona_gray joins her predecessor @demileighnp , @thandohopa @zintathu and @connie_ferguson to choose Miss South Africa 2019. A post shared by  Miss South Africa (@official_misssa) on Aug 5, 2019 at 6:43am PDT THE OFFICIAL JUDGES! Reigning Miss Universe @catriona_gray joins her predecessor @demileighnp , @thandohopa @zintathu and @connie_ferguson to choose Miss South Africa 2019. A post shared by  Miss South Africa (@official_misssa) on Aug 5, 2019 at 6:30am PDT THE OFFICIAL JUDGES! Reigning Miss Universe @catriona_gray joins her predecessor @demileighnp , @thandohopa @zintathu and @connie_ferguson to choose Miss South Africa 2019. A post shared by  Miss South Africa (@official_misssa) on Aug 5, 2019 at 6:28am PDT THE OFFICIAL JUDGES! Reigning Miss Universe @catriona_gray joins her predecessor @demileighnp , @thandohopa @zintathu and @connie_ferguson to choose Miss South Africa 2019. A